    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-06-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <head>86. Presidential Review Memorandum/<gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                        >NSC</gloss>–37<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d86fn1">Source: Carter
                        Library, National Security Affairs, <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1"
                            >Brzezinski</persName> Material, Subject File, Box 12, Chemical Weapons,
                        5/78–11/80. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-06-16">June 16, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Vice President</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <head>ALSO</head>
                    <item>The Director, Office of Management and Budget</item>
                    <item>The Director, Arms Control and Disarmament Agency</item>
                    <item>The Chairman, Joint Chiefs of Staff</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Chemical Weapons (U)</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has directed that the Special Coordination Committee undertake a
                    review of the United States chemical weapons (<gloss target="#t_CW_1"
                    >CW</gloss>) posture incorporating information acquired over the past year and
                    covering the following:</p>
                <p>1. An update on the <gloss target="#t_CW_1">CW</gloss> threat, U.S. protective
                    posture and U.S. retaliatory capability.</p>
                <p>2. An assessment of the current bilateral negotiations with the <gloss
                        target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss> aimed at the preparation of a joint <gloss
                        target="#t_CW_1">CW</gloss> initiative for presentation to the Conference of
                    the Committee on Disarmament (<gloss target="#t_CCD_1">CCD</gloss>)
                    including:</p>
                <p>—Key elements on which some degree of agreement has been reached with the <gloss
                        target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>.</p>
                <p>—Key elements on which agreement has not been reached, and possible approaches
                    for resolution.</p>
                <p>—Prospects for agreement on a joint initiative consistent with the current U.S.
                    negotiating instructions.</p>
                <p>—Consideration of extent of implementation of past decrease regarding U.S. <gloss
                        target="#t_CW_1">CW</gloss> stocks.</p>
                <pb facs="0223" n="192" xml:id="pg_192"/>
                <p>3. In light of the assessment per Paragraph 2, a review of the <gloss
                        target="#t_PD_1">PD</gloss>–15 decision<note n="2" xml:id="d86fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d70">Document 70</ref>.</note> “that U.S. chemical warfare
                    forces be maintained without force improvement” including a discussion of
                    possible steps to modernize or restructure the U.S. <gloss target="#t_CW_1"
                        >CW</gloss> posture.</p>
                <p>The review should be completed by July 14, 1978.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
